parameters: Ceres: Leon-san! It's been a while.

Leon: Lady Ceres, it has indeed been a while. I fondly remember the
days when I, as an instructor, imparted swordsmanship in Moduna.

Ceres: Yes. I was surprised to hear that you are now a general of
Valentina, Leon-san.
Leon: Well, a lot has happened.
Ceres: ......

Ceres: By the way, Leon-san... I've heard rumors that the supreme
commander of the Valentina army in Jupiterino is Lord Zena.

Ceres: Can you somehow ask Lord Zena to negotiate a ceasefire with
them?

Leon: Understood. I will pass on the message, but I doubt Lord Zena
will be receptive. Please don't get your hopes up.
Ceres: Is that so...

Ceres: Leon-san, there is a blue mage named Luuna. With Luuna, you
stand no chance of victory. She is an old friend of mine.

Ceres: Luuna is determined to defeat you and Lucia. She's risking her
life to stop Lucia's tyranny.
Leon: Luuna? Are you referring to that blue mage?

Ceres: I won't ask why you are in Valentina, Leon-san, but if anyone
can persuade Lord Zena and the Valentina army, it's you. I don't want
Luuna to die.

Leon: Regardless of Hilda, Lady Sylvia will likely not agree. And I
doubt Lord Zena will readily listen to what I have to say.
Ceres: ......

Leon: However... since it's a request from an old friend like you,
Ceres-dono, I will convey it to Lord Zena. We also do not wish to
battle the Knights of Messiah.
Ceres: Please do whatever you can.
Leon: Yes. Forgive me. With this, I must take my leave.
Ceres: ......

Vice-Captain: Was that Leon? His demeanor and manners, not to mention
his formidable swordsmanship, were quite impressive.

Ceres: Yes. Leon-san is a formidable swordsman. It doesn't seem likely
that we can expect much from persuading Lord Zena... but we've done
what we could.

Ceres: All that's left for us to do is to watch over Luuna, as there's
not much else we can do.
Ceres: Luuna...

Luuna and her companions headed towards the towering iceberg in front
of the city of Norvania, "Vilac's Iceberg."
